SYMPTOM_TEXT: About two weeks after vaccine symptoms began, fatigue, shortness of breath.  Second dose 3/14/21. Body aches began about 7 hours after vaccine for the next 24 hours.  Fatigue and shortness of breath continued and began to have pain when taking deep breaths.   3/23/21 went to Urgent Care and had chest x-ray which was negative.  Feeling worse later that night went to the Emergency Room. Had EKG , blood work up and covid test.  Covid test was negative.  Troponin levels elevated  0.74, 0.130, 0.97.  I was admitted to the hospital for observation and further tests.
LAB_DATA: Chest x-ray negative, ECG showed a sinus rhythm with a left anterior fascicular block and generalized ST-T wave changes. Coronary angiography showed no significant narrowing.  4/23/21 MR Cardiac W Contrast showed normal LV chamber size no evidence of MI fibrosis or infiltrative disease. No significant valvular disease.   Clinical picture consistent either  with myoericarditis or pleuritis. Medications prescribed 0.5  colchicine and ibuprofen. 7/27/21 NM Lung Scan Perfusion Particulate.
OTHER_MEDS: Multivitamin, Claritin, aspirin, omeprazole 20mg, Flonase, Lisinopril 10mg, progesterone 200mg, estradiol 0.0375mg

In September 2021, 2 weeks after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced lip dry, rash, swelling of limb and generalized pruritus. On an unknown date, the outcome of the lip dry, rash, swelling of limb and generalized pruritus were unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the lip dry, rash, swelling of limb and generalized pruritus to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The pharmacist reported that the patient received the Shingrix and a non-GSK flu vaccine on the same day and experienced dry lips, rash on arms and torso, swelling in limbs, and overall itching. The patient did not have any symptoms until 2 weeks after his vaccines. The reporter spoke per content and referred patient to healthcare professional. The reporter did not consent to follow-up.

told her not to get the 2nd dose; chest pain in heart; shortness of breath; extreme fatigue; Myocarditis; staying in bed the whole time; inflammation; she wasn't feeling better; pericarditis; started feeling weak; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of ANGINA PECTORIS (chest pain in heart), DYSPNOEA (shortness of breath), ASTHENIA (started feeling weak), FATIGUE (extreme fatigue), PERICARDITIS (pericarditis) and MYOCARDITIS (Myocarditis) in a 22-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The patient's past medical history included COVID-19 (Patient had Covid 19 over the summer and her symptoms began on 1st week of July with a positive Covid test on July-2021) in July 2021. In September 2021, the patient experienced ASTHENIA (started feeling weak) (seriousness criterion disability), PERICARDITIS (pericarditis) (seriousness criteria disability and medically significant), BEDRIDDEN (staying in bed the whole time), INFLAMMATION (inflammation) and MALAISE (she wasn't feeling better). The patient was treated with COLCHICINE for Inflammation, at a dose of .6 milligram twice a day. At the time of the report, ANGINA PECTORIS (chest pain in heart), DYSPNOEA (shortness of breath), ASTHENIA (started feeling weak), FATIGUE (extreme fatigue), PERICARDITIS (pericarditis), MYOCARDITIS (Myocarditis), BEDRIDDEN (staying in bed the whole time), INFLAMMATION (inflammation) and MALAISE (she wasn't feeling better) had not resolved. It was reported that on 08-Sep-2021, 18 to 20 hours after the 1st dose, patient started having chest pain in her heart, shortness of breath, extreme fatigue. She went to urgent care on 08-Sep-2021, the doctor diagnosed her with myocarditis and prescribed steroids. About a week and half after the symptoms began, she wasn't feeling better even after staying in bed the whole time, started feeling weak and went to see the 1st cardiologist who diagnosed her with pericarditis after doing an echocardiogram and EKG. Three days later she went to a 2nd cardiologist to get a 2nd opinion. He diagnosed pericarditis as well after looking at the same echocardiogram and prescribed treatment to alleviate the inflammation. The 2nd cardiologist also did 2 blood tests to check for damage and blood clotting. The 2nd cardiologist also told her not to get the 2nd dose and that it would take about 6 months for the inflammation to go away.   Most recent FOLLOW-UP information incorporated above includes: On 30-Sep-2021: Follow up received and included no newinformation; Sender's Comments: This case concerns a 22 year-old female patient with reported history of covid-19, who experienced the unexpected serious events of dyspnoea and angina pectoris, and the expected but serious events of pericarditis and myocarditis. The event occurred 2 days after the first dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine for all the reported events, whit the exception of pericarditis, which occurred a week and a half after vaccination. The rechallenge was unknown for all the events, since they are not recovered/not resolved, and no information about second dose is provided. The medical history of Covid-19 infection remains as a confounder and a risk factor for the events of myocarditis and pericarditis. The benefit-risk relationship of mRNA-1273 vaccine is not affected by this report.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: entire body rash. started on forearm as a vesicular rash on erythematous base. no improvement with topical steroids.  quickly spread to upper right arm as sand paper rash the size of a softball to inner upper arm.  Then large erythematous firm purple tinged almost bruise like on right flank.  another on right inner lower leg.  all rashes of slightly different appearance and inconsistent.  itching, painful, warm.  spares hands and feet and face.  worse with heat, better with cold. no relief with oral or topical meds/steroids.  injection on right arm and all rash symptoms on right side of body.  no other constitutional symptoms.  present for 4 weeks with minimal improvemnt.       pt had previous reaction to HPV vaccine with several weeks of hives and therefore didn't complete the series.  was trying to avoid covid vaccine for fear of hives again but was forced to get vaccinated at place of employment.  first vaccine no reaction, second dose caused the rash
ALLERGIES: sulfa.  previous allergy to HPV vaccine that was hives related

neuropathy; shingles; This initial spontaneous report was received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation referring to a female patient of unknown age. In or around April 2012, the patient was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (lot#, expiration date, dosage, route of administration and anatomical location were not provided) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). On an unspecified date, shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient suffered shingles and neuropathy.  As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient's symptoms have resulted in physical limitations and seriousness of her condition. As a result of the zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), she sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence, the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. The outcome of shingles and neuropathy was considered to be not recovered. The reporter considered shingles and neuropathy to be related to Zoster Vaccine Live (ZOSTAVAX).  Upon internal review, the events of shingles and neuropathy were determined to be disabling.  Upon internal review, the event of neuropathy was determined to be medically significant.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 09/10/21:  Patient is a 57 y.o. male with recent COVID infection, HFpEF, NASH cirrhosis, CKD IIIb, and IDDM2 who presented to ED via EMS post-code after PEA arrest. According to patient's wife, he developed acutely worsening shortness of breath early this morning. Wife called EMS after his shortness of breath did not improve upon resuming his home oxygen 3L NC which he had discontinued two days prior due to subjective improvement. Family estimates he stopped breathing less than 5 minutes prior to EMS arrival. EMS reports patient was apneic and in wide-complex PEA on arrival. He was coded for 20 minutes before ROSC. He arrived intubated and on levophed.    Cardiogenic etiology considered due to transient hypoxia; however troponins without significant delta, EKG did not show ST abnormalities concerning for ischemia, or MI. Bedside echo without concerning findings. Infectious workup negative. Aggressively diuresed patient with minimal renal recovery. On exam patient was lacking gag reflex and pupils unreactive. Due to concern for severe anoxic encephalopathy and PVS, all sedation was stopped. Patient remained without any purposeful movement, without gag reflex, and without reactive pupils after >48 hours of complete cessation of sedating agents. Poor prognosis discussed with wife (NOK) and daughter. They both stated he has previously said he would not want to continue with current measures in this type of situation. Wife (NOK) ultimately decided to withdrawal care and pursue comfort care. Patient was terminally extubated and discharged to inpatient hospice
LAB_DATA: COVID PCR positive for covid on 8/23/21 and 9/10/21
CUR_ILL: On 8/23/21:   57-year-old male with PMHx of NASH cirrhosis, CKD, type 2 diabetes with peripheral neuropathy, and hypertension presented as a direct admission from outpatient cardiology appointment.  He was admitted to medicine for management of volume overload suspected secondary to chronic kidney and liver disease.  On initial admission he required up to 6 liters NC to maintain SPO2 greater than 88%.  His resp decline was felt to be multifocal related to both his COVID infection as well as to pulmonary edema secondary to his known NASH cirrhosis, CKD, and HFpEF. He completed a five day course of remdesivir (stop date 8/29/21) and will continue dexamethasone for a total of ten days (stop date 9/3/21). SYMPTOM_TEXT: Consented to a Flu Vaccination through my Employee Health Department.  I went in at my scheduled time and was sent to a room.  The nurse in the room told me to come have a seat.  I told her I was there for a Flu Shot.  She said OK and then asked for my Covid Vaccination card.  I then again stated "I was there for a Flu Shot".  The nurse said "Yea, I still need it".  I gave her  my card, she never asked any other questions like my name, date of birth, employee number, etc... and then stuck me with a vaccine.  She said I could leave and then I asked if I should grab a t-shirt off the table for receiving my Flu Shot.  She then asked if I had a flu shot yet.  I said "Yes, you just gave it to me".  She then said "What?"  I asked "What did you just give me?"  She responded, "The Covid Booster".  I was so angry because I got pretty sick from the 2nd Covid vaccine and that the reason I did not want the Booster.  We then went to management and I spoke with them.  I also filled and incident report with Hospital and so did my boss.  Before I left Employee Health was was also given my Flu Vaccine by management.  This all took place on Thursday, Oct 7th and by Saturday, Oct. 9th, I had to make a trip to Urgent Care.  I was very dizzy, had a horrible headache, very fatigued, my heart was beating so fast and I was having a bit of trouble catching my breath.  I reported all of this to Employee Health this morning Oct. 11th and I am waiting on a response.

Within the first week of receiving the 1st dose of Moderna, out of the blue I would start feeling pressure in my forehead -around my eyes and then my heart would start fluttering and feel like it was up in my throat and I would feel dizzy and nauseous.  This happened several times within the 2 weeks after getting the shot.  All my life I have had low blood pressure - but these episodes made me think my blood pressure was spiking! After I received the 2nd dose 28 days later - within days, the "blood pressure" episodes started happening daily and several times a day. Sometimes I feel like I am going to faint when this happens.  This is when I looked up "heart fluttering/blood pressure" to figure out what was going wrong as I have always had low blood pressure!  That's when I saw that heart inflammation was a side effect of the Moderna vaccine!  All the symptoms described was what I was experiencing!!  After 2 weeks of the 2nd dose, it seemed like the episodes had dwindled... but last week - October 6-8 - I started experiencing these symptoms again and I really hate the feeling of my heart fluttering and like it is in my throat and the feelings of weakness & nausea that follow.  These episodes lasted for half an hour or so!!!  I thought these symptoms would go away after a couple of weeks after the vaccine but now 6 weeks later, I am still experiencing them!
LAB_DATA: I have not yet gone to the doctor about this because I was hoping it would subside but now i will probably make an appointment with my family doctor to check into this further as I don't want to develop high blood pressure and heart problems when I had neither prior to August 3 and August 30, 2021 - when I got the 2 Moderna vaccines.
HISTORY: None - I have always had low blood pressure.

On the 5th of March, in the morning, I was going about my normal day and I noticed that I didn't feel right. I did my normal morning routine. I started to drink my coffee and it started dribbling out of my mouth. I went to the bathroom and saw my face in the mirror. It appeared as if I could not smile on the left hand side of my face. I stuck my tongue out and it came out straight. Since it came out straight, I thought that maybe I was in the beginning stage of a stroke. I got in my car and drove myself to ER. I was taken to the back right away after explaining that I thought I was having a stroke. They performed a CT scan and knew right away that it was not a stroke that I was having. I was released with a prescription for prednisone and diagnosed with Bells Palsy. When I spoke with my pharmacist, and told her about my prescription, she told me that she has not ever seen this many cases at one time of Bells Palsy. I am currently having persistent double vision. I will see my optometrist again in November.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My first dose was 4/19/2021. My second dose was 5/21/2021. Within an hour of my first dose, I started to develop a very intense and severe headache in my forehead that lasted for days. This was probably the worst headache I've ever had, incredibly distracting, very painful, was hard to get any work done or do anything while it lasted. It lasted for days and slowly subsided over several weeks. About 1-2 weeks after my first dose, I started to notice some cognitive changes in myself. I wasn't understanding a simple joke a friend said, when normally her humor is very easy and I have never had issues with her jokes in the past. Another friend I confused dates of plans, when normally I am very organized with my calendar and timing, but suddenly I was having a hard time keeping track of days of the week and dates. She noticed it as well. Over the next few weeks and months, it got worse. Suddenly I wasn't able to retain information I had just heard - for instance I was in class and a teacher would tell me something. I would hear her, understand what she said, repeat it to myself, and promptly forget a minute later. One occasion, I asked a question and the teacher reminded me she had just said that information (yet somehow I couldn't remember it). This has happened multiple times with my boyfriend as well - I ask him something, he responds, I forget his response immediately and I forget I even asked, so I ask my question again. He reminds me I just asked, at which point then I remember I asked, but I forget his reply. He has commented multiple times on my memory issues. My mother has also noted my memory issues and has commented on them. I forget conversations we have - for instance I was supposed to teach her how to tint her eyebrows. The conversation happened, and yet I totally forgot it happened. I asked her a week later if she wanted me to teach her how to tint her brows and she paused and then reminded me that I already had. This is extremely unlike me. I am known in my family and friends for having an excellent memory. My earliest memories date back to when I was 17 months old, and yet suddenly I had this awful headache after my first vaccine dose and now I have trouble remembering something I heard 3 minutes prior. I can't retain information. This has affected my work, my earning ability (I had the worst quarter I've ever had this last quarter), my schooling (I forget what I learn). I have also messed up the order of words and numbers. For instance, I will invert an idiom unintentionally, so instead of writing "stone cold," I'll write "cold stone" and not realize it until later when I re-read an email I sent. I will sometimes add verb endings to nouns by accident - for instance if I am trying to say I was reading a book, I might say "read a booking." I won't notice until later when I re-read what I wrote. This is a problem because these emails are going out to clients! I have also inverted numbers in sales quotes, a huge problem considering that I work in sales and what I quote and sell is my livelihood. Luckily I have caught myself most times, but there have been times I have inverted something that was supposed to be in the tens into the hundreds place and vice versa and that impacts my quotes! I reported all of this to my doctor in August, they had a virtual appointment with me in September, and then referred me to the cognitive neurology department. I have recently gone through cognitive testing, and I am waiting for the results in two weeks.
LAB_DATA: Cognitive testing - 9/28/2021 MRI I believe has been requested but has not taken place yet.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 70 y.o. male who presented with frequent falls from his mobile home. PMHx of end-stage renal disease on hemodialysis TThS, hypertension, coronary artery disease, hypoxic brain injury during CABG, cognitive impairment. The patient presented with generalized weakness and increased falls at home.    The patient was admitted with right lower extremity cellulitis and placed on cefazolin. The patient has known severe PAD likely contributing to ulcerations but has declined revascularization in the past. An US of bilateral lower extremities was performed which showed a right lover extremity thrombus within a right intramuscular vein in the mid calf. Anticoagulation for this alone is not warranted. Over the course of the hospitalization the patient showed improvement in erythema and completed total 7 day course of antibiotics.    The patient was also incidentally found to have COVID-19 infection. He is vaccinated and was initially asymptomatic. He later developed SOB and wheezing at which time CXR showed bilateral infiltrates and he was started on Decadron 6mg daily and albuterol. Patient remained on RA and completed course of Decadron.    Overall, the patient has a documented history of medical noncompliance. He is a poor candidate for anticoagulation due to frequent falls. Anticoagulation was discontinued. He was placed on Plavix due to his severe PAD.    Nephrology followed along while inpatient to continue patients outpatient dialysis schedule.    On morning of discharge, patient was found to be slightly hypothermic but asymptomatic. He was briefly placed on Bair-Paws and temperature improved and remained stable off warming devices. He did have a mild leukocytosis which was felt to be reactive from steroids. He had no complaints on day of discharge and felt great. He was discharged to SAR in stable condition.

Twelve hours after my booster shot I developed fever, chills, aches, and severe headache, which lasted over twelve hours.  The second day I ached all over, but I felt better on day three.  At midnight on day 4 (Saturday) I had a leg vein open and bleed uncontrollably.  I had to use Blood Stop to stop the bleeding.  I saw my vein doctor the following Monday, and he injected the vein to shut it down.  That same week I developed a worsening of my arthritic knee--much more pain and loss of mobility.   It feels like burning nerve pain from my knee down to my ankle and up to my hip.  It hurts to even drive my car.  A few days after that I began having terrible tooth pain on the upper AND lower left side teeth.  Two of those top teeth already have root canals.  The lower teeth have repairs.  The pain slams my face and radiates to the front teeth.  I saw my dentist.  His X-rays did not show anything conclusive.  I saw the periodontist.  His X-rays didn't really show anything either.  I have a visit scheduled with my endodontist this week to evaluate the roots and try to determine where the pain is coming from.  The pain is debilitating.  I've begun Advil around the clock to keep it from becoming overwhelming.  I have no idea if any of this is related to the vaccine.  But it all came on within days of the shot.  As a nurse, I'm wondering if I've mounted an inflammatory response that is causing me all this pain.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Wed 9/15 I had normal COVID side effects (sore arm and feverish) but in addition I had a large amount of blood in my urine (urine was raspberry red).  This continued through Thursday and into Friday morning.  I called the clinic on Friday morning and was directed to the Express clinic.  At the clinic, I provided a urine sample and the results were that all of my parameters (with the exception of blood in the urine which was large) were normal and there were no signs of infection.  The doctor recommended that I go to the ER for a CT scan which I did that evening.  The CT scan was negative for kidney stones and they could not see any abnormalities.  Therefore, they referred me to a Urologist on on 9/23/21 at 10 am.  Another urine sample was collected and still contained blood although not to the extreme of the previous week.  Cellular abnormalities were not detected.  The urologist recommended a urology cytoscopy which has been scheduled for 10/27 where they will check my bladder, urethra, etc.  I have seen 2 doctors and been to the ER as a result of this event.  I did not receive any other vaccines on 9/14.
LAB_DATA: A basic metabolic panel from blood - 9/17, urine culture - 9/17, urinalysis chemistry- 9/17, urinalysis (micro) - 9/17, CT scan kidney - 9/17, cytology urine - 9/23, urinalysis auto 9/23
OTHER_MEDS: Simponi (50 mg/month), Methotrexate (10 mg/week), L-thyroxine (25 Mcg/week), folic acid, calcium & vitamin D

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At around 4:00 p.m. the same day of receiving the vaccine I started feeling slightly dizzy which progressed. Went to bed early evening to lie down, assuming possible side effect from vaccine.  Also felt very slight feeling of nausea. I got up a couple of times to go to bathroom and still felt slightly dizzy as I walked into bathroom each time. Overnight, but before morning found myself sweating a lot as if I might have a fever. It was not hot in the loft where I was sleeping; however. I changed into a tiny slip. By the next morning I felt better but was still slightly dizzy when I sat up in bed. I started to feel less dizzy as the morning progressed and got up to eat mid morning. Between 1:30 and 2:30 p.m. Saturday (the following day) I felt fine and went outside. I called my insurance company's 24-hour nurse on Saturday but have not yet contacted doctor. During time I felt dizzy  as a precaution I would not have gotten into my car to drive anywhere and did not feel bad enough to call taxi to go anywhere either.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day following my second vaccine I started having chest pain on the right side of my chest where my lung is. I felt it was my lung so I assumed it was because of my asthma and me having been outside a lot the day prior. It persisted so I made an appointment with my primary health provider, but I couldn?t get an appointment for a month.  The chest pain lasted the entire month and occurred every day, but wasn?t constant. Besides the chest pain I could breath fine except I felt like I couldn?t fully empty my lungs.  She listened to my lungs and they sounded fine, but ordered an X-ray. The X-ray showed just a little fluid in them so she ordered an ECHO. The echo showed cardiomyopathy so she referred me to a cardiologist.   All my bloodwork is fine. Dr said I had significant heart failure with EF less than 30% alone with the cardiomyopathy with mild enlargement of left ventricle. I don?t have high cholesterol and my BP is only mildly elevated when I go to the dr, but at home it tests fine.  I am obese. I had a cardiac MRI a month later (was the earliest they could get me in).  The mri already showed EF improvement to 45% and nothing was enlarged.  I had a stress test a couple weeks later and it showed no blockages. The cardiologist has put me on Entresto for the heart failure and a beta blocker to slow my heart to give it time to heal. She put me on these right after I had the ECHO.
LAB_DATA: Lung X-ray 6/11/2021 ECHO 6/16/2021 ECG 6/23/2021 Bloodwork 6/30/2021 Cardiac Mri with stress test 7/21/2021 Stress treadmill test 8/9/2021 Bloodwork 8/13/2021
OTHER_MEDS: Albuterol, vitamin d, singulair, Zyrtec, omeprazole, ibuprofen

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Admitted to Hospital on Date of Adverse Event [recorded in VAERS] for treatment of Covid-19 Positive following completion of Covid Vaccine Series

From the seventh day, fatigue continued. I just felt not well and then I realized that I felt pressure in my chest and heart and a loss of appetite. I barely got around each day. I had to ask neighbors to walk my dog because I didn't have the energy. I was finally able to see my cardiologist on Feb. 27th, I was in A-fib, he prescribed me Eloquis and Flexicide. He ordered an Echo and put me on a 2-week heart monitor. I went back a week later and they started me on another medication and changed the way I was taking Flexicide. I still feel crappy. I went in on March 16th, he looked at my background and Echo results and I had elevated pulmonary pressure and still in A-fib. He started me on Lasix and said he wanted to do a heart catherization. They found only one 80% blockage and put a stent in. My 2-week heart monitoring showed I was in A-fib the entire two weeks. I went back for follow up April 6th, I was still in A-fib and they sent me for an ablation. I went to the doctor for the ablation on April 27th. The ablation was successful but I had a slow recovery. It was the end of August before I started feeling normal again.
LAB_DATA: EKG; Echocardiogram; Heart monitor; Heart catherization; Ablation
PRIOR_VAX: Sore arm from Tetanus and Shingles vaccine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Three days after my 2nd shot, I had some cramping/ period pain at night on June 11th. Strange and out of the ordinary as I have regular periods. the next day, the 12th I began bleeding. I bled for 5 days. The blood looked different than normal mentstrual blood and I did not have any regular period pain with the bleeding.  Then I got my 'regular' period on July 1st and had it longer than usual, 7 + days. There was very heavy bleeding at the beginning and for a longer time than usual. Usually heavy bleeding lasts 1-2 days, this lasted 3-4 days.   Then I had bleeding on July 28th, just once and then none the next day. Had more bleeding and cramps on the 30th, but not like usual and then my 'normal' period came the next day, the 31st.  Period started again on August 28th.  Did not get a period in September. Period started again on October 2nd and it seemed 'normal.'
LAB_DATA: I told my GP and he scheduled a pelvic ultrasound and I had that on September 7th at 5pm and everything came back 'normal. '

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fever 101.9 degrees, body aches, joint pain, and chills. Took Tylenol.

I first noticed that I had an irritated feeling in my nose. I had been having a sensation in my nose for a few weeks before. About four days later I got a Petechia rash on my lower calf It was about 5 inches big. Later that day my husband started coughing. We were on vacation with a group staying in the same house. People started to having symptoms all of a sudden, and everyone had been vaccinated. We isolated away from those showing symptoms. I got a sore throat, headache and coughing. I got a blister rash on the corner of my mouth. I then got a fever and a very bad headache. My fever was 102 which was very high for me. I had dizziness, sweating and chills as well as loss of appetite. I experienced Brain fog and lost my sense of taste and smell about a week after the onset. The loss of taste and smell lasted for about 5 days. When it returned it seemed like smells were unpleasant for two days. My sense of taste returned after that but now even seven weeks later I still have times when I can't taste anything salty. About five days after onset on 08/17/2021 I had Tachycardia and I was out of breath. The coughing was constant. My Oxygen was low and I was hospitalized on 08/21/2021 and I got Monoclonal Antibodies on 09/23/2021. The day after I got the Regeneron antibodies I started to feel better and two days later my brain started to feel less foggy. It has been seven weeks and I still having a little trouble with brain fog, forgetful and disorganized.
HISTORY: Trigeminal Neuralgia; Fibrocytes in both Lungs; IBS
PRIOR_VAX: Fluzone-Anaphylaxis

Client reports that over the next few days the rash progressed and spread up toward the trunk of her body. About 8 days after receiving the vaccine she had this hive-like rash covering her entire body. Client reports that the rash was hot to the touch, burned, and itched. Client reports she was seen on 9/10/2021 where she was prescribed 4 days of prednisone and topical triamcinolone cream. Client reports no symptom improvement so she went to a specialist on 9/13/21. Client reports they ran tests and biopsy's which did not show cause for the rash. Client was treated with a longer course of prednisone, topical betamethasone, and hydroxyzine. Client reports the dermatologist told her the rash was from the vaccine, and that she could call the government agency. PHN referred client to her PCP to determine course of action for 2nd dose of vaccine. Client verbalized understanding. Client reports rash improvement, but still experiencing hives on her trunk to date.

Per ED Note: History of Present Illness   Patient is a 74-year-old female with past medical history of bronchitis, diabetes mellitus, hypertension and hypothyroidism presenting to the emergency department with chief complaint of cough and shortness of breath.  Patient states that she has been experiencing cough, dizziness and difficulty breathing for approximately 1 week.  She went to her PCP and was prescribed cough medicine with codeine and an unknown antibiotic but has not experienced any significant relief of her symptoms.  She states that the shortness of breath is worse with exertion and alleviated by rest.  She states that the cough is productive of clear sputum.  Patient states that she is received both of her COVID-19 vaccines and denies any known sick contacts.  Patient denies headache, blurry vision, fever, chills, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, chest pain, abdominal pain, numbness, weakness or tingling her extremities. ED Course/Medical Decision Making:     The evaluation, management, services and procedures as well as the key components of the patient's care described here in were performed in the presence of the attending physician.  Old E-care/clinical records were reviewed.   Pulse oximetry interpreted by me: 89 % room air - normal    Initial vital signs are stable.    ED Course/Reevaluation:   Labs -COVID-19 rapid test is positive. Creatinine 1.3 mg/dL.   Imaging -  Bilateral peripheral predominant airspace disease suspicious for viral pneumonia.  Congestive heart failure changes with diffuse interstitial edema.   EKG -ventricular rate 91 bpm, PR interval 170, QRS 74, QT/QTc 340/418, normal sinus rhythm.   ED Course -patient presents with complaint of shortness of breath for 1 week.  Physical exam significant for a tired appearing patient, clear lungs bilaterally, otherwise unremarkable. Upon arrival patient was hypoxic at 89% and required supplemental oxygen to bring her SPO2 to 93%.  Patient also received an albuterol/Atrovent breathing treatment with some improvement in her shortness of breath.  Basic labs obtained are significant for positive COVID-19 rapid test, acute kidney injury (creatinine 1.3 mg/dL).  CXR demonstrates bilateral peripheral predominant airspace disease suspicious for viral pneumonia and congestive heart failure changes with diffuse interstitial edema.  EKG is normal.  Patient was treated with Lasix 10 mg.  This patient symptoms are most likely related to COVID-19.  I recommended to the patient that she be admitted for her acute hypoxia requiring supplemental oxygen and she agrees.  I contacted this patient's PCP and the on-call physician, and she accepted the admission with request that the patient be evaluated by infectious disease as an inpatient. Patient demonstrates understanding and agrees with the diagnosis and plan. Patient is well appearing with stable vital signs.  Admitted to inpatient. Final Impression:
Vaccine was diluted with the sterile water instead of Normal saline. Manufacturer was called and told to not repeat dose of vaccine. Pt reports no adverse effects post-vaccination.
Tested positive after both vaccines

I initially woke up with intense burning/pain on my forehead.  Over the next few days, the site of the pain became red, swollen, and blistered.  I went to the urgent care at Hospital on September 11.  They thought I had a skin infection (but could possibly be Shingles) and prescribed antibiotics.  The antibiotics were not helping and the blisters were spreading (across my face, around my eye, under my hair--all on the right side) so I went to a different urgent care location on September 13.  They told me that it looked like I had Shingles and prescribed Valacyclovir 1000 mg twice/day.  That started helping, but the Shingles persisted for quite a while.  I also had to visit an eye doctor because the Shingles were around my eye.  He prescribed additional medication for me, which I am still taking now (Acyclovir).  Two out of the three doctors I saw said that this could have definitely been triggered by the vaccine.  Consequently I was not able to get the second dose, and I'm not sure that I want to.  While my immune system was down because of the Shingles, I ended up contracting COVID.  I am currently fighting that as well.
LAB_DATA: September 11:  Urgent Care visit (given antibiotics) September 13:  Urgent Care visit (given Valacyclovir) September 13:  Urgent Care visit (later filled a prescription for Acyclovir when the Shingles persisted) October 3:  Positive COVID test  October 4:  Antibody Infusion

Itchy - in the evening; itchy all over my whole body; and restless due to the itchiness. I was hot but didn't have a fever. About 8 pm, I had a rash all over my back. It was hives and large red inflamed area. It was itchy, too. That was the only place where I had a visible rash. I was able to reach the doctor on-call at my primary care practice that Saturday night (telemed). I sent him a picture - he said it was an allergic reaction to the vaccine ( a delayed skin reaction). He told me to take Benadryl and to go to ER if I had trouble breathing. I didn't have to go to ER as I didn't have trouble breathing. The Benadryl helped with the itching. The rash stayed there close to a week. The Benadryl did improve it and I took it for another 24 hours. On the 22nd, I went to Urgent Care  (the same phone number as my doctor) and the rash was real still really visible. They prescribed a topical ointment (steroid) and that was helpful. It was still itchy but not as bad as before I used that - it was more like a normal mosquito bite after using it. Dr. at Urgent Care said it was definitely an allergic reaction. He also prescribed an oral steroid which  I didn't take. Two months later, I had to have an MRI with contrast dye - as soon as the contrast dye went in I couldn't breathe - they had to pull me out of the machine. And then I developed the same exact rash (same size and shape, even) that I had had after the 1st vaccine. I went to my Primary Care Dr, and she also prescribed me the same topical steroid which I used. It took about a week for that rash to resolve. I wasn't as itchy as I was with the first time (after this COVID shot). They sent me to an Immunologist. With  having cancer, I've had a lot of MRI's with contrast and never had a reaction before. That doctor thought the vaccine had activated my immune system to be more reactive. Steroid and an Histamine - to premedicate with that before I take the Booster shot next week.
LAB_DATA: Two months later, I had to have an MRI with contrast dye - as soon as the contrast dye went in I couldn't breathe - they had to pull me out of the machine. (It  was an MRI for my breast, I think.)
OTHER_MEDS: Lisinopril - 5 mg; 81 mg Aspirin; Vit B; Vit D; Xanax
ALLERGIES: Tetrytol; Dilantin; Azithromycin; Tenoxicam; Kiwi Fruit

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 52 year old female with past medical history of hypertension, DM type 2, pituitary adenoma, presented to ED for nausea, vomiting, fever, cough and unable to tolerate anything PO. Symptom onset was 9/24, she works as a nurse, got tested for COVID Friday 9/24, rapid test was negative, retested Monday 9/27 due to worsening symptoms which resulted positive. Nausea and vomiting persisted and patient become short of breath which prompted her visit to the ED on 9/29. Patient required 3 L of oxygen and was given IV Phenergan for her nausea which helped. She was also started on Remdesivir on 9/30 and Dexamethasone on 9/29. She was started on Lantus and Lispro for BG control. Her hospital course was marked by increasing oxygen requirements which prompted a D-dimer, which was negative for suspicion of DVT/PE. Pt had worsening oxygen requirement of up to 7L, and a D-dimer that doubled, so CT-PE ordered on 10/03 and was negative for PE. Patient continued to improve clinically with lessening cough and oxygen requirement. A walking home O2 evaluation showed that she needed 3 L to maintain on O2 saturation of 88% while ambulating. Patient completed both her Remdesivir and Dexamethasone course while inpatient.  Admitted 10/1/21 and discharged 10/8/21
HISTORY: PMHx of GERD, HTN, and DM2,

On August 5, 2021, I had a biometric screening at work which my blood pressure was 164/110.  It was retaken 4 times with rest times on both arms, same result.  I was told to schedule a doctors appointment to address my blood pressure.  I had an appointment on 8/11/2021 which my blood pressure was high.  I was placed on blood pressure meds, Losartan at 25 mg.  My blood pressure was rechecked and the results were still high.  I was increased to 50 mg of Losartan. I have another visit scheduled in December.

I was told to email you to report an adverse event that happened to our patient .  Event happened 9/28/21.  Pt came in to get her Pfizer booster shot during her visit. One MA reconstituted the vaccine and another administered it. The next day when another booster was to be given to a different pt, the MA who reconstituted the vaccine the day prior was watching another MA doing it and realized that she had done it wrong on the previous day.   The MA thought that the Pfizer Covid 1- vial was a single dose vial so she took the 1.8ml of of the diluent and divided it amongst the 6 vaccine vials thinking they were single dose. The MA drew up the vial and administered the entire content to the patient for a total of 6 doses and .3ml of diluent.   The provider was made aware and he called the patient to inform her of the incident and to ensure there were no adverse reactions that the patient would need to come in for. Pt stated that she was just having localized soreness around the vaccine site. the provider advised patient to call our office if any symptoms become severe.   Discussion with the team included what had happened as well as what we can do to prevent the issue from happening in the future. We agreed that whenever possible we will have the clinic RN reconstitute and draw up the vaccines and if not available we will have 2 MA present during the reconstitution and drawing up of the vaccines as a double check. RN will check off all MAs from start to finish on reconstitution process. This was also reported to VAERS and the state.
Unilateral lip swelling started 10 days following vaccination. No other suspected causes.

August 20 or 21st, I woke up in the morning, with a loud snap in my head. Like a firecracker went off. I grabbed my husband to wake him up. I felt fine after. I go up and made some coffee. I went online to see if anyone else has had this. I found a couple of websites; EHS, Exploding Head Syndrome. I read about it and it said many people, especially women over 50 do. It doesn't cause adverse affects or any problems. They sited four things that might cause it: stress (I don't have); lack of sleep (that's not me either); inner ear problem (I had just finished an antibiotic for an earache, a few days to a week before, I had finished that medicine). I can't think of what the fourth cause was. I haven't had it again. Three or four days later, I went to the doctor for my annual check-up. My doctor was very concerned. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the vaccine on August 26th at about 1330. I initially felt ok, but started to get tired around 1930 and decided to crawl in to bed. Shortly after, I broke a fever and my body was starting to feel achy. As I starting to fall asleep, my body started to feel tingly. This was alarming, but as I continued to try to fall asleep, I felt as if my body was ballooning over my body, like an out of body experience. This terrified me so I got out of bed and started pacing back and forth, afraid to fall asleep in fear of this out of body like experience happening again.  After pacing for as long as my body could, I laid back down again, and began to feel the tingly again which then turned to the numbness. I sat up and turned the light on and decided that trying to sleep was not a good idea. I sat there as my body went numb again, and this time felt the numbness in my brain. Even more terrified now, I paced for hours occasionally needing to lay down on the floor in child's pose (the only comfortable position for my very achy, fatigued body, and now also the worst headache I have had in my entire life). I was unable to stop moving for long as the body numbness would set in again shortly after I would stop moving. I was then experience muscle spasms/jerks in my arms. When I was finally able to lay down long enough to fall asleep, I would wake myself up crying due to the terrible headaches. Thankfully my numbness was better the next day. The headaches stayed for days. Dizziness for weeks.

I was put on Dexilent twice a day with minor relief. I again went to see my Gastro Dr. and no firm diagnosis was made. After having nausea and stomach pain since March, which got progressively worse, I changed Dr. with the hope he may be able to make a firm diagnosis. He suggested I repeat the endoscopy as the first one showed more that a "mild inflammation" which I proceeded to have on September 30, 2021. After the results he suggested that I see a Hematologist/Oncologist as he suspects it is a blood disorder. On October 7, 2021 I had numerous vials of blood taken and the end result is  Auto Immune Gastritis, a complicated inflammation of the stomach. I also am told my blood test revealed that I have antibodies for Pernicious Anemia .I follow up with an endoscopy every year and never was diagnosed with Auto Immune Gastritis or that my stomach issue was related to a possible blood disorder. My belief is that it was caused by my Moderna Vaccination and is definitely an after effect of it, which I have to follow up on for the rest of my life.

I got my vaccine on 9/27/2021 around 5 pm in order to keep my job, which I started several months ago. The first night I felt mostly fine apart from soreness in my right arm where I was injected. I woke up the next day and felt like a truck hit me - exhausted, weak, fever/chills and tingly skin. I stayed home from work to rest and take care. Later that day the soreness in my upper right arm subsided and my hands felt very itchy, notably between my right thumb, index and middle fingers. I tried to avoid itching. I went back to work on Wednesday the 29th and felt mostly better apart from my arm still itching. Over the course of the next week the itching turned into a tingling/numb sensation that travelled from my fingers into my hand. As I write this now at the keyboard, my entire right arm is tingling and numb. Using my right hand for extended periods of time is a challenge. I am a healthy, 31 year old, active person with a plant-based diet and very health conscious. I'm worried these side effects have not gone away. I do not have a doctor yet and am awaiting health insurance.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: For the first dose, I broke out into a rash & had some shortness of breath (I forgot to mention that I have mild asthma.) The staff on site gave me Benadryl and observed me for 30 minutes. They said it was a mild, immediate reaction, but that it would be safe to receive my second shot. For the second dose, I had shortness of breath, broke out in a rash, had a fever of 101.3, had nausea, vomiting, dizziness, deep fatigue, weakness, exacerbation of joint pain, clamminess, muscle pain, severe headache, etc. I was sick for 7 weeks post vaccination. My rheumatologist- who had encouraged me to be vaccinated because of my being immunocompromised- prescribed a two-three week course of steroids because he told me that about 60% of his female patients who received the vaccine were ill like I was. He said if the steroids didn?t work, he would consider further treatment/hospitalization. The steroids helped with some of the most acute symptoms. One of my other physicians prescribed antibiotics, a powdered inhalation disc to help improve my breathing, and Tramadol for all of my aches and pains. We?re not certain that I have permanent issues as a result of the vaccinations, but I haven?t felt ?quite right? since.
LAB_DATA: Bloodwork. Most of the results were within normal limits.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was administered the first Moderna Covid Shot (Lot #010M20A) on 2-11-2021 and the second shot (Lot#026A21A) on 3-11-2021. I felt no reaction from either shot except for mild arm soreness where the vaccine was given. This soreness disappeared within a day or two.  About a week after receiving my second shot of Moderna, I started having mild chest pains. I did not relate these pains to a Covid shot. On the evening of March 31, 2021, I was feeling tired and told my wife I would take a bath and go to bed, which I did. I couldn't get comfortable in bed as my chest was hurting, so I got up and sat to watch TV for a while. While sitting up, the chest pain went away. I went back to bed, and the chest pain intensified anI went back to bed, and the chest pain intensified and was radiating down my left arm. I got up and told my wife I thought I was having a heart attack. She immediately drove me to the hospital, where I was admitted to the Emergency Room and given a battery of tests. At 5:00 AM, I was admitted to the hospital overnight for more testing. On April 1, the diagnosis was pericarditis. The hospital doctor prescribed Colchicine which I took daily. On April 25 I sent a message to my Dr., my Cardiologist: I wanted to update you on the status of my symptoms. I have been taking an antibiotic ( Doxycycline Hyclate 100 MG) for the past three weeks. Today I ran out of the prescription. It doesn't seem to matter as I have continuously hacked up sputum all day for the past three weeks. The anti biotic doesn't seem to be doing any good. Also my pericarditis used to be causing me pain only when I lay on my back in bed. For the past week, it is causing me pain in my chest and shoulder when I stand or sit. It is not severe pain, but it is there. It appears to be getting worse. I have run out of my Ibuprofen prescription and have been taking Advil (three 200 MG pills). I had an appointment with Dr. (Rheumatologist) on 4/27 and she seemed to believe that my heart issue was associated with my upper chest condition. I have an appointment with Dr. (Pulmonary) on May 4. Medication doesn't seem to be helping. Any suggestions?  I just want to confirm with you that you are taking the Colchicine daily as well? Thank you, RN.  Yes, I am taking the Colchicine daily, but as I indicated, my chest pain seems to be getting worse, not better. My chest pain is there even if I am not lying down. It is not severe, but it is there when I breathe.  On May 4, 2021, I visited Dr., a Pulmonologist, for coughing up yellow sputum. He prescribed a PredniSONE taper and scheduled a complete pulmonary function test in late June.  On July 8, I visited Dr., and he stopped the prescription for Colchicine as he believed the pericarditis was resolved. Also, on July 8, I saw Dr., Pulmonologist, and he believed my upper chest infection had been resolved, but scheduled a full pulmonory test on my lungs which was done on July 28. It showed my lungs were clear and breathing normally. "This test showed no obstructive or restrictive ventilatory defect. Overall, lung volumes are normal. Diffusion capacity is also normal."

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Nausea and vomiting, died in her apartment 2-3 days after COVID-19 Moderna 2nd shot administered. On March 25, 2021, our daughter received her first COVID-19 Moderna vaccination. On April 22nd, she received her 2nd Moderna vaccination, and our daughter grew ill and died in her apartment alone 3 days later. On April 23rd she telephoned to Inform my husband and I that she was nauseous and vomiting, and that she Informed her doctor of her symptoms. She said, her doctor told her that her symptoms where normal and should subside within a few days. On April 26 at 2:27 pm she was pronounced dead and her body was transported to the coroners office. The doctor on staff, wrote the cause of death as Atherosclerotic Cardiovascular Disease. Considering the fact that she was fine prior to taking the COVID-19 vaccine, my husband and I questioned cause of death. How was/is he able to say for sure that the 2nd COVID-19 vaccination was not the/a contributing factor to her death, particularly withstanding the absence of chain of events leading up to her death? His response literally was "I've seen so many cases like this, and I know what they look like. I can just look at a patient and tell what the cause of death was." This is a major concern for us, how could he know for sure without knowing anything about our daughter's medical history? Our daughter was a young 52 aged female with no prior history of heart disease, and she was well, up until receiving the 2nd COVID vaccination. Our hearts are crushed, she took very good care of us. We are seniors, and she was a major part of our lives, she prepared our meals. went grocery shopping, visited a minimum of 4 times weekly...We loved her so and she loved us. Sincerely, parents of deceased

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was fine for the first 4 days after the vaccine aside from a sore shoulder. On the 4th day, I started having chills. I had a temperature of 102.3. My skin got very blotchy and white, which they called mottling. It would last 3-4 hours. As quickly as it started, it went away, and I felt like I was on fire. My temperature dropped to 94 and I was shaking. Then 3-4 hours after that I was halfway back to normal. I had an upset stomach and couldn't eat. Over the 15 days this lasted, I lost 15 lbs. I went to the doctor and a COVID test which was negative. The doctor advised to continue with the Tylenol and Advil because he was unsure what to do. Every 3-4 hours, this cycle would start all over again. During the fever, my hands would turn white as if they got frostbite all the way up my arms. All of this went away miraculously about 3 days before my 2nd dose. I was feeling good for those few days. Since then, I have had difficulty breathing, pain in my back and center of my chest. I also have lack of energy, and headaches. I went to the doctor where a chest x-ray was done. The x-ray came back as possible pneumonia. I was sent for a CT which showed thickening in the lungs. I was then sent for a stress test, echocardiogram which both came back normal.
HISTORY: Diabetic (on insulin pump); Heart condition; Stomach problem

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Hospitalized 09/30/2021; COVID-19 positive 09/30/2021; fully vaccinated  Patient is a 72-year-old female presents the chief complaint of fever, fatigue, shortness of breath.  Upon initial evaluation she is hypoxic to 86%.  Placed on 2 L nasal cannula with good response.  COVID-19 testing is positive.  She has an AKI evident on CMP.  Lactic acid slightly elevated 2.2.  She is given 2 L IV fluids for her AKI and lactic acidosis.  She does not have a history of decreased EF.  Chest x-ray is consistent with COVID-19 pneumonia.  She is given 6 mg IV Decadron.  I spoke with the hospitalist who agrees to admission and further management of this patient. Assessment/Plan  DIAGNOSIS at time of disposition: 1. Pneumonia due to COVID-19 virus  2. Hypoxia  3. Respiratory insufficiency  4. AKI (acute kidney injury)  5. Lactic acidosis  10/3/2021 note:  ASSESSMENT / PLAN: Pneumonia due to COVID-19 virus Assessment & Plan Continue remdesivir, inhaled steroid, inhaled beta stimulant, inhaled Spiriva, supplemental oxygen, empirical antibiotic coverage as well given the presence of elevated procalcitonin. She received dexamethasone on hospital day 1 when she was still in ER and then she became confused and agitated, she threatened to leave AMA on hospital day 2 at 7a.m., she was agitated.  She did calm down subsequently and I have found out that she does tolerate small amounts of inhaled steroids but not oral steroids.  Therefore I switched to the available in the hospital equivalent of  Trelegy she takes as an outpatient specifically Dulera and Spiriva  plus p.r.n. albuterol. Vitamin C, zinc are also being given. DVT prophylaxis Acute respiratory failure with hypoxia  Assessment & Plan Continue high-flow nasal cannula oxygen, she is saturating 93 up to 95% on 60 L, plus non-rebreather, FiO2 is 100%.  If she worsens then next step would be intubation 10/8/2021 note: Assessment/Plan: Pneumonia due to COVID-19 virus Assessment & Plan Will continue with present medical regimen.  Will give a dose of Lasix today 10/05/2021 will give dose of Lasix today.  Also talked her about the steroid issue.  She wants to try it again.  I thought I had given to her orally my diet have the same subjective feelings that she has been getting with the IV steroids 10/06/2021 her D-dimers markedly elevated at 11,000 thousand.  I have empirically started her on heparin drip.  Will send her down for a CT angiogram.  Will also schedule her for upper lower extremity Dopplers.  Clinically she says she feels better today than she did yesterday. 10/07/2021 initially she had an elevated procalcitonin question of an infiltrate.  Procalcitonin has normalized but there is consolidation at the mention on her CT scan.  I decided to continue broad-spectrum antibiotics for now.  In light of her declining respiratory status will move her to the intensive care unit 10/08/2021 she finished remdesivir, she is refusing the empirical antibiotic coverage.  Will check a procalcitonin in the morning.  She is on the inhaled steroid but she refused the intravenous Solu-Medrol. 10/08/2021 the patient stated to me and also she stated in no uncertain terms to the previous physician that she does not desire intubation in case that she deteriorates to that point.  I do intend to honor this and she is therefore a do not resuscitate.  However it should be noted that she is now maxed out on nasal cannula high-flow oxygen plus non-rebreather and she is saturating marginally in the low 90s at best.  I made her daughter aware of these and I also discussed extensively with the daughter when the that the prognosis is guarded in this patient with COVID pneumonia and pre-existing severe chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. Note from 10/11/2021: 10/09/2021 the patient is saturating marginally on 60 L of oxygen per nasal cannula plus non-rebreather however now she is pleasant and cooperative with the medication therefore this is a bit plus compared to yesterday 10/10/2021 the patient is doing a bit better oxygen saturation wise on the same supplemental oxygen she was on yesterday.  She is conversational and speaks in longer sentences before being short of breath.  She refused the Lovenox therapeutic but she is okay with the heparin drip.  Afebrile. 10/11/2021 I consulted virtual intensive care unit, I appreciated very much their input, the patient is not a candidate for intubation given her chronic obstructive pulmonary disease history.  She in fact refused intubation as a concept this morning but then she reconsidered that however after discussing with the pulmonologist the patient again admitted to not wanting intubation and this is in fact inappropriate decision given the advanced emphysema that the patient is suffering from. Noted 30% of predicted DLCO 2 years ago.  Noted persistent oxygen needs of 100% via high-flow nasal cannula 70 liters/minute.  Noted marginal saturation.  As per pulmonologist's recommendation will decrease the steroids to twice daily.  She is off antibiotics since she completed course.  Right now I have her on heparin drip, twice daily steroids, supplemental oxygen.  Prognosis is guarded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was 3 days into my menstrual cycle when I received the vaccine. Normally by day 4 my bleeding would get very light almost spotty in nature rather than a constant bleeding. By day 9 it was extremely heavy with a serious amount of large, golf ball size clots. Bleeding was so heavy and has been since receiving the vaccine that when going to the bathroom it sounds like I am voiding rather than changing a tampon. The super plus tampons and a heavy pad are saturated in less than 2 hours and to date it has just got to the point that a super plus tampon will last 2 hours and will be leaking before that 2 hours is up. My normal menstrual cycle lasts a max of 5 to 6 days with the last two days being spotty not even a light consistent flow.  I have had a severe headache for 2 weeks now and nothing is helping it at all. Have been to the GYN and my PCP and nothing else is wrong that could be causing this so I was instructed to file this because it is an adverse reaction. I am also a Nurse and will be forced to take the 2nd injection in 8 days and with the wax the bleeding is still going, I will more than likely still be bleeding when I get the 2nd injection. Somebody has to study this and make sure this doesn't happen to others and figure out how to change the FDA approved vaccine so that it doesn't do this for the future injections we have to get.  Thanks
LAB_DATA: Going to GYN for the 2nd time on 10/14/2021 to try to get meds or an implant to stop the bleeding. They are not sure if it will work or not but we are going to try

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was 7 months pregnant at the time that I was taking my second dose of the Covid-19 Vaccine. My due date was April 20th. On Thursday, February 18th I got my 2nd dose. That morning, I had been checked by my doctor and had  a 32 sonogram and everything was deemed healthy. On Friday, I felt achy and had slight fever- I attributed it to the vaccine and took it easy that day, resting. On Saturday, I was still achy. I also started having Braxton hicks contractions (or so I thought) around 12 pm. I was achy and not feeling well all day and again attributed that to the vaccine. Early Sunday morning (2/21) around 12:30 am, I realized that my braxton hicks contractions were increasing and getting worse. By the time I realized I was in labor it was 2 am.  We rushed to the hospital and I had my son at 32 weeks. The adverse event is that I gave birth 8 weeks early and that my son had to spend 2 weeks in the NICU just days after receiving my second dose. (In my previous two pregnancies, my body had never gone into labor itself. I had to be induced.)

Called online nurse consultant for advice and was told to visit urgent care if symptoms worsen.    Patient did not seek additional care that night.  Next morning , symptoms continued with dizziness, lightheaded, SOB.  That afternoon, headache turned into "migraine" - went home to sleep. He referred me to a rheumatologist.  It took me 5 months to get into her and my pain was the same She diagnosed me as having Rheumatoid Arthritis caused by the Single injection. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Toward the evening and night of that same day I started to feel sick. I took some ibuprofen, and then went to bed. Around that time I started my period and it was a lot heavier. However, I did get a birth control implanted in my arm a  few months before getting the vaccine. Since then my period has gotten less and less. After about a week of getting the vaccine, I started to feel back pain with two muscles in my back that would hurt.

The night I got my vaccine, I started to experience muscle twitching in my left leg.  This was a month ago and I experience muscle twitching daily all around my body - leg, buttocks, feet, eye, face.  I went to my doctor about this and got blood work done and all my labs were normal.  My doctor suggested I see a Neurologist if the twitching doesn't stop.  I have never experienced muscle twitching before the vaccine.

The first dose of the vaccine was fine.  Just felt a little ill.  The second dose was terrible.  I woke up the next day and felt like there was a block of concrete in my arm and shoulder.  I couldn't move it at all.  I had flu-like symptoms for about 5 days, which resolved on its own with no issue.  The arm and shoulder, on the other hand, did not resolve.  I had very little range of motion, painful shooting pains when the arm and shoulder were used, and there was swelling.  I could not get dressed, wash or brush my hair, cook or clean, lift anything or complete even the most simple tasks at work.  Driving was very difficult.  Sleeping was nearly impossible. After 4 months and deciding that my arm and should were not going to get better on their own, I went to my PCP where I was told I had bicep tendonitis and adhesive capsulitis (frozen shoulder).  My PCP thought it was caused by the vaccine being injected into the joint in the shoulder rather than the muscle.  She provided me with pain medication and I was referred to an orthopedist.  Dr did a thorough examination, took ex-rays, gave me a cortisone injection, and sent me to physical therapy.  He didn't know if the issue was caused by giving the vaccine in an incorrect location or if it was just my body's reaction to the vaccine.  After several weeks of physical therapy and very little improvement, I had shoulder manipulation surgery and another injection of cortisone.  I was provided with pain medication and I had physical therapy every day for another two weeks.  I'm at about 90% mobility now.  It is extremely unlikely I'll ever be back to 100%.  I can perform most day-to-day tasks with little to no pain.  I continue with daily physical therapy exercises at home.  My pocket book is still hurting.
LAB_DATA: 7-1-21 PCP Evaluation, 7-13-21 Ortho Evaluation, 7-13-21 X-rays (negative for breaks), 9-8-21 Shoulder Manipulation Surgery, 9-24-21 Ortho Evaluation

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediately after getting the vaccine, I felt a rush. I felt a little lightheaded, but I was okay on my drive home I felt very lightheaded and dizzy. I almost fainted in the car. I felt like my vision was weird. I don't see double, but I feel that my vision doesn't line up like it used to. I think this is permanent. This happened within 20 minutes. I also got vertigo within 20 minutes as well. After that, it felt like I was on a boat. If I turned my head too fast things moved too quickly. I felt off balanced as if I was in a boat. I felt tired and sick as well. After the vaccine I also got severe headaches and head pressure. I also experienced tinnitus and my ears felt as if they were spasming inside. This has gotten better over a few months and went away. I do still get headaches more often. The vertigo waned over a few months and is now basically gone. The first night after the 1st dose, I also had a pounding heart palpitation which I usually get when I am really sick. For my second shot, within 24 hours, I had sore arm, nausea, fatigue etc which all went away in a few days.  I saw an NP for the vertigo who told me to take Ativan which helped significantly. I then found out that you need to stop taking the Ativan in order for your brain to cure the vertigo. So, I stopped taking the Ativan and within 3 days, it had improved and eventually went away. I am supposed to go for a full vestibular testing (4hrs) but I feel I am okay for now so I have put it off. Based on his full evaluation, he suggested I have vestibular neuritis.  He said that this happening so soon after the vaccine, it was possible the vaccine could've caused it. One morning in August, I had blurred vision in my right eye. I went to the ER but it had resolved by the time they evaluated me.
LAB_DATA: neuro exam (balance etc)  physical therapy for vertigo
CUR_ILL: bad cold sore in my mouth accompanied with headache, tingling/burning, ill feeling
PRIOR_VAX: Flu Shot, rush feeling same as after COVID vaccine, dizzy for 15-20 mins after

After the first and second shots I was sore and tired, which I expected. Later, however, in August 2021 I noticed my resting heart rate seemed to be higher than normal and on my job as a volunteer firefighter there were rare occasions when I felt like I might not be able to go on and that my heart couldn't keep up (it didn't come to a medical emergency, and I was able to rest and feel better). Although these calls were particularly fatiguing incidents for everyone and it's to be expected that I'd feel awful with the smoke and exertion, I don't remember ever feeling like that in any other instance. In addition, in my EMT class when we would have our pulse rates taken constantly so others could practice, mine was consistently in the high 80s at best to low 100s at its worst. None of that was normal for me a year ago or before my shots. My only guess is that I either screwed something up through firefighting, I'm having side effects from the shot, or a combination of both. I feel totally and completely fine otherwise. It hasn't slowed me down or caused pain, I just have noticed an increased heart rate which isn't normal but does not seem to negatively affect me or my abilities.

April 11, in the morning (8am) I woke up with a heavy feeling in my chest. Pain in my right arm, I also had flu like symptoms. My head hurt and I was coughing. My whole body was aches and pains. I was cold and hot, and I was in bed for a week. On the 14th, I went to the ER . They did a lot of tests ? ECG, (high), BP 160//100, a chest xray which was normal, a lot of blood tests and nothing came abnormal, troponin was .04. everything came back normal and the only thing that was abnormal was my blood pressure. The doctor said they didn?t find everything and said to follow up with primary doctor. I didn?t think anything of it at the time so I went back to my normal routine. I noticed that I was out of breath a lot, so I figured it was maybe old age. As I progressed more and more, every time I walk up a flight of stairs, I?m tired. This is where I got worried. I work out 5-6 times a week with pilates and hikes with my girlfriends with no issues. And now I?m no longer able to do that. That was my main concern. On 9/23/2021, I wasn?t feeling well so I reached out to my doctor, I called & texted him and he wanted to do a video chat. He asked me if I had a BP machine, so I took my BP and took it and showed it to him ? 161/102. He said you needed to go the ER but I didn?t want to go. The last time I went, there was nothing found. He said the BP scared him and I went to the ER on 9/23. On that day I went to the ER and its packed. They said it would be a long wait, but that was fine. They took my vitals and they said my BP was way too high. I sat at the ER for 3 hours. They finally called me to the back & checked an ECG and there were abnormality. They took my oxygen and said my heart wasn?t getting enough oxygen. They ran a stress test on my heart and took a lot of blood for tests. Some came back with some info, but the bottom line was they couldn?t tell me why my blood pressure was so high and why my heart wasn?t getting enough oxygen because it was strong. I talked to my doctor to see what else he could do. I was in the ER for about 2 days, they didn?t admit me but they held me there for 2 days. They were overwhelmed with patients. I followed up w my doctor on 9/29 . We did another virtual doctor visit and he ordered an inhaler for me called Albuterol 90. He told me to use the inhaler when I needed it the most. He also ordered me to follow up with a pulmonologist and I have an appointment with them on 11/11 at 1pm . I still can?t catch my breath, even when I?m talking. I?m trying to go back to working out and I can only do 1 hour a day because that?s all I can handle. A constant pressure in my chest, I can?t catch my breath. There has been times where if I gasp for breath too hard, I get a sharp pain in my chest and I get concerned. My breathing is starting to get harder and harder. I know from talking to other people who have had the same vaccine that they have the same problems.
LAB_DATA: 4/14 - ECG, (high), BP 160/100, chest xray (normal) blood panel (normal) except for the troponin 0.04, CBC lymphocytes 41 (high), absolute basophils 0.0  9/23- 161/102, ECG - abnormality, oxygen levels were low,  blood panel,  creatine ratio 7.8, stress test on the heart (normal) MPV - 7.3 absolute basophils 0.0 troponin 0.05 (high) lipid panel - cholesterol 5.3 basic metabolic panel - calcium 10.7 (high) bu 8.8 (low)

Intraparenchymal hemorrhage (May 2021);  Vaccinated (January / February 2021 with Moderna) Patient reported this as an Adverse Reaction via reporting system  Discharge Provider: Primary Care Provider: Admission Date: 5/28/2021 Discharge Date: 5/30/21 Active Hospital Problems:  Intraparenchymal hematoma of brain (HCC);  Spontaneous intraparenchymal intracranial hemorrhage, acute (HCC)   PRESENTING PROBLEM: Brain bleed (HCC) [I61.9] Spontaneous intraparenchymal intracranial hemorrhage, acute (HCC) [I62.9]   HOSPITAL COURSE: A 42 year-old that presented with headaches and olfactory auras with a head CT that demonstrated acute to subacute right mesial temporal intraparenchymal hemorrhage with a rim of surrounding edema. CTA was negative for vascular pathology and MRI Brain with and without contrast demonstrated small developmental venous abnormality arising near hematoma with drainage to vein of galen, otherwise stable hematoma and edema. Patient was given a loading dose of 2g of Keppra and then started on 750 mg Keppra BID. Patient underwent a diagnostic cerebral angiogram which revealed "early opacification of a prominent cortical vein near the mesial temporal region without definitive arteriovenous shunting. Perihematomal hyperemia versus a small underlying mass cannot be excluded". A continuous EEG reading was negative for seizures. The patient was otherwise voiding, ambulating, and tolerating an oral diet, thus deemed medically stable for discharge with follow-up as above.   CONSULTS / RECOMMENDATION: Neurology: patient to follow-up resident clinic for AED management. On maintenance Keppra dose 750 mg.
LAB_DATA: INPATIENT PROCEDURES: 5/30/21: Diagnostic cerebral angiogram.  5/30/2021: No seizures recorded. No epileptiform activity or evidence of focal cerebral dysfunction was seen.  The new MRI from June 2021. Interval significant improvement in the anterior right temporal lobe hematoma/hemorrhage when compared to May 29, 2021 with a persistent small region of enhancing heterogeneous signal. Significantly improved and likely resolved associated parenchymal edema. As before, the adjacent developmental venous anomaly could be the etiology of hemorrhage. Consideration should also be given to an associated cavernoma.  The associated enhancement is favored to be related to a vascular abnormality and/or granulation, however follow-up is recommended to evaluate evolution and exclude an enhancing mass

Patient received COVID-19 booster vaccine (Pfizer) on 9/25/21. On 9/27 she reported generalized weakness, not getting out of bed or eating for 2 days. On Wednesday 9/29 she went to Urgent Care for a COVID-19 test which was negative and a chest CT was ordered. There were findings of effusion so she was referred to the emergency department. Upon presentation to the emergency department, the patient was hypotensive, experiencing new onset atrial fibrillation, and requiring 2L oxygen. Cardiology was consulted and advised to monitor with telemetry. The following morning 9/30/21 the patient denied chest pain, shortness of breath, palpitations, and dizziness. A pericardiocentesis was completed on 9/30/21. Post-procedure the patient remained hypotensive and complained of mild chest tightness. The following day, the patient reported shortness of breath and a nonproductive cough. The patient was started on colchicine 0.6 mg BID. The patient's statin was continued. On 10/2/21, metoprolol was added for rate control for atrial fibrillation and patient reported cough and wheezing. On 10/3 the patient was started on Eliquis 5 mg twice daily for stroke prevention and did not complain of cardiac symptoms. The patient had no further cardiac complaints on 10/2 and 10/3/21 awaiting procedures for cardioversion. The patient tolerated the procedure and did not complain of chest pain, shortness of breath, palpitations, cough, or wheezing. On 10/6/2021 the patient was stable for discharge. She was discharged on home medications with the addition of metoprolol tartrate 25 mg twice daily, Eliquis 5 mg twice daily, colchicine 0.6 mg twice daily, and an albuterol inhaler. Her home amlodipine was discontinued.  She was instructed to follow up outpatient for further monitoring.

I also have the exact same sore throat I had in March 2020 when I thought I had covid - fever, shortness of breath, sore throat, cough -- but I did not qualify back then for a test because of the shortage of tests available. That evening (early on), I took a nap and went to roll over and my arm wouldn't even come. I had to lift it and move it myself, it was the right arm. It was a 10 pain wise. It was unbelievable. That went on for two months before I could lift it on my own. My doctor said that I was hit in the bursa muscle because it was not moving. That evening also I got a fever that went up to 101. I had total flu like symptoms. Body pain, aches and couldn't open my eyes. Those symptoms lasted for about 36 hours until I could finally get out of bed and start to function again. A week after the vaccine, my neck started to be stiff where I couldn't turn it all the way, couldn't turn it to left or right. It is still that way. (Started on the right side and then it was my entire neck) and I still notice now that it's difficult to turn my neck. Physically, my entire body changed with pain. Still today, my gait is off; my left groin, I have to have help getting my leg lifted up to get into a car. I never had body pain before. I have trouble lifting my left leg. No treatment except ibuprofen on occasion. I take it when I am in bed and can't get out of bed due to a lot of discomfort. They recommended physical therapy, I can't start yet because I'm in so much discomfort. I can't do the therapy yet. I do try to lift it on my own without assistance but it doesn't work. I went to see a neurosurgeon because my pain started to vibrate to the hips and lower back. He told me I just have to deal with it because there is not much he can do about it. He said I could take gabapentin but the side effects are significant and I do not want those side effects.
LAB_DATA: I got my back checked and my spine because my pain from neck went to my spine. They found nothing wrong in neck, MRI of my neck and back and upper groin area. My primary care doctor or my heart doctor ordered it.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 1 week following vaccination the patient developed daily fever up to 103� F, diffuse joint pain and myalgia, severe headache, drenching night sweats, and fatigue.  The symptoms persisted for 8 weeks prior to presentation to my office with prior workup at previous PCP.  She ultimately developed erythematous nodular rash in addition to the above symptoms.  I obtained a punch biopsy of this and it resulted with findings of neutrophilic dermatosis consistent with either palisaded neutrophilic dermatitis or possibly consistent with Sweet's syndrome.  The patient was started on prednisone for this and had initial improvement in rash but had subsequent relapse.  At this time she has been referred to Rheumatology, Dermatology and Neurology.  She has been initiated on dapsone for attempted steroid sparing regimen for treatment of her rash however she continues to have daily fever, headache and night sweats.
LAB_DATA: The patient has had extensive serologic testing for underlying rheumatologic disease with no evidence of underlying lupus, rheumatoid arthritis, or vasculitis.  Inflammatory markers were initially significantly elevated with ESR of 97 and CRP of 7.9, which improved following steroid taper.  Infectious etiologies were evaluated with HIV serologies, QuantiFERON testing for tuberculosis, multiple blood cultures, lumbar puncture, and urinalysis without evidence of underlying infection identified.  CBC was obtained without evidence of blood dyscrasia and serum protein electrophoresis obtained without evidence of multiple myeloma.  Extensive imaging was obtained with MRI of the brain and cervical spine with and without contrast obtained.  CT of the chest abdomen and pelvis with and without contrast was also obtained showing some adrenal nodules but no obvious infectious or neoplastic processes noted on these.  Patient has been referred to ENT for evaluation for atypical presentation of giant cell arteritis which was felt to be unlikely.  She has been referred to Gastroenterology and is preparing for upper and lower endoscopy to rule out any possible GI based malignancy. I have ordered 24 hour urine metanephrines given persistent symptoms to rule out pheochromacytoma.
